description.narrative: By 2025, Primary health and referral facilities enhanced to provide equitable, high-impact and high-quality MNCAH services across the continuum of care including in emergency settings, which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 'By 2025, newborns, children, adolescent girls and women benefit from an equitable, high-quality and resilient health system across the continuum of care

description.narrative: Novel Oral Polio Vaccine type 2 (nOPV2) vaccination was successfully introduced, and national Polio campaign conducted reaching 16, 970, 321 children.165,000 sick newborns benefitted from 79 hospitals where UNICEF supported neonatal intensive care (NICU) Level III equipment and clinical mentorship.; Health services were provided to 827,224children and to womenaffected by conflicts through support to 119 mobile health and nutrition teams. Care of sick children was enhanced through training of456 HEWs in integrated Community Case Management of newborn and childhood illness in five regions and 159 health workers in Integrated Management of Neonatal and Child Illnesses (IMNCI). | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:07/01/2022
